{"cursor":"3425","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox terrorist attack |title=Hadera central station suicide bombing |image=\n|caption= |map= 'The attack site' |location=Hadera, Israel\n|coordinates = |target= |date=April 13, 1994 9:40 am (GMT+2) |time-begin= |time-\nend= |timezone= |type=Suicide attack |fatalities=5 (+1 suicide bomber)\n|injuries=30 |perps=One Palestinian suicide bomber (Amar Salah Diab Amarna).\nHamas claimed responsibility. }} The 'Hadera bus station suicide bombing' was a\n1994 Hamas suicide attack on a passenger bus departing from the central bus\nstation in Hadera for Tel Aviv, Israel. Six were killed and 30 injured. The\nattack came exactly one week after another Hamas attack, the Afula Bus suicide\nbombing. The attack took place on the Israeli Fallen Soldiers and Victims of\nTerrorism Remembrance Day.\n\nHamas bombmaker Yahya Ayyash built a bomb using two kilograms of home-made\nacetone peroxide explosive. Twenty-one-year-old Amar Salah Diab Amarna, a native\nof Ya'bad in the West Bank, was selected for the mission. Katz, p. 108\n\nOn the morning of April 13, 1994, Amarna boarded the 9:30 AM bus to Tel Aviv. At\n9:40 AM, as the bus was pulling out of the station, Amarna placed the bag\ncontaining the bomb on the floor of the bus, \"where shrapnel could rip through\nvital arteries in the groin area,\" and detonated it. Katz, pp. 108â109\n\nAs Israeli rescue workers converged on the scene of the explosion, a second pipe\nbomb exploded. Hamas later claimed responsibility for the\nattack. [http://www.ujc.org/content_display.html?ArticleID=4965 Suicide and\nCar Bomb Attacks in Israel Since the Declaration of Principles (September\n1993)]\n\n' Fatalities' [http://www.mfa.gov.il/MFA/Terrorism-\n+Obstacle+to+Peace/Palestinian+terror+before+2000/Fatal+Terrorist+Attacks+in+Is-\nrael+Since+the+DOP+-S.htm Fatal Terrorist Attacks in Israel Since the\nDeclaration of Principles (September 1993)] {|\n|\n* Bilha Butin, 49\n* Rahamim Mazgauker, 34\n* David Moyal, 26\n|\n* Daga Perda, 44\n* Sgt. Ari Perlmutter, 19\n|}\n","linknr":186,"url":"Hadera_bus_station_suicide_bombing","recorded":1375071978,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Hadera_bus_station_suicide_bombing&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Hadera_bus_station_suicide_bombing&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/File:Israel_outline_center_ta.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ed/Israel_outline_center_ta.png/250px-Israel_outline_center_ta.png","/wiki/File:Red_pog.svg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/0/0c/Red_pog.svg/7px-Red_pog.svg.png","/wiki/Hadera","/wiki/Israel","/wiki/Geographic_coordinate_system","//tools.wmflabs.org/geohack/geohack.php?pagename=Hadera_bus_station_suicide_bombing&params=32_26_7.03_N_34_54_48.68_E_","/wiki/Greenwich_Mean_Time","/wiki/Suicide_attack","/wiki/Hamas","/wiki/Hamas","/wiki/Suicide_attack","/wiki/Hadera","/wiki/Tel_Aviv","/wiki/Afula_Bus_suicide_bombing","/wiki/Yom_Hazikaron","/wiki/Yahya_Ayyash","/wiki/Acetone_peroxide","/wiki/Ya%27bad","/wiki/West_Bank","#cite_note-1","/wiki/Groin","#cite_note-2","/wiki/Pipe_bomb","#cite_note-3","#cite_note-4","/w/index.php?title=Hadera_bus_station_suicide_bombing&action=edi